<body>
    <header>
        <h1><marquee behavior="alternate";bgcolor="yellow";height="1000" >Vegan Stir Fry</marquee></h1>
    </header>

    <section>
        <h2>Ingredients</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>1 cup tofu, cubed</li>
            <li>2 tablespoons soy sauce</li>
            <li>1 tablespoon sesame oil</li>
            <li>1 tablespoon vegetable oil</li>
            <li>1 onion, sliced</li>
            <li>2 bell peppers, sliced (use different colors for visual appeal)</li>
            <li>1 cup broccoli florets</li>
            <li>1 cup snap peas, trimmed</li>
            <li>3 cloves garlic, minced</li>
            <li>1 tablespoon ginger, grated</li>
            <li>3 cups cooked brown rice or quinoa</li>
            <li>Salt and black pepper, to taste</li>
            <li>Green onions and sesame seeds for garnish</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Instructions</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>Marinate the tofu cubes in soy sauce for at least 15 minutes.</li>
            <li>In a large wok or skillet, heat sesame oil and vegetable oil over medium-high heat.</li>
            <li>Add marinated tofu to the hot oil and stir-fry until golden brown on all sides. Remove tofu from the wok and set aside.</li>
            <li>In the same wok, add sliced onions, bell peppers, broccoli, and snap peas. Stir-fry for 3-4 minutes until the vegetables are crisp-tender.</li>
            <li>Add minced garlic and grated ginger to the vegetables. Stir-fry for an additional 1-2 minutes until fragrant.</li>
            <li>Return the cooked tofu to the wok and add the cooked brown rice or quinoa. Toss everything together until well combined.</li>
            <li>Season with salt and black pepper to taste.</li>
            <li>Garnish the Vegan Fried Stir with green onions and sesame seeds.</li>
            <li>Serve hot and enjoy your delicious Vegan Fried Stir!</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

